cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes an energy-efficient transmission scheme for wireless sensor networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The proposed scheme involves closed-loop feedback process to divide the network into logical regions, which can be seen as a multiagent system. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a control scheme to adapt the transmission power level based on link quality changes, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses open-loop temperature-aware link quality estimation and compensation, which involves information theory concepts. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the proposed scheme can have implications on the security of wireless sensor networks, as it involves transmission power level adaptation.
